section.section:
An insurance company or its insurance producer may sell or dispose of a motor vehicle knowing that the identification number of the vehicle has been removed, if:
The vehicle is the subject of a total loss settlement by the insurance company;
The Administration will not issue a distinguishing number under § 13-106.1 of this article;
The insurance company or its insurance producer determines that the vehicle is not rebuildable; and
The transfer is to a licensed automotive dismantler and recycler or licensed scrap processor.

An insurance company or its insurance producer may sell or dispose of a motor vehicle knowing that the identification number of the vehicle has been removed, if:
The vehicle is the subject of a total loss settlement by the insurance company;
The Administration will not issue a distinguishing number under § 13-106.1 of this article;
The insurance company or its insurance producer determines that the vehicle is rebuildable;
The transfer is to a licensed dealer, licensed automotive dismantler and recycler, or licensed scrap processor; and
The transferee is advised that the vehicle may not be offered for resale to any other person until after the vehicle has been assigned a distinguishing number under § 13-106.1 of this article.
